summary: Number cruncher with thorough background Statistics/Machine learning, data management, and -visualization with various statistical packages (R, Python, SQL, Stata...). Continuous learner with differentiated knowledge in social and behavioral science as well as regarding (research) methodologies. Excellent analytical and logical reasoning, constructively critical manner of thinking. Outstanding skills in sharing and incorporating ideas in group projects as well as presenting them in a consistent and interesting way. I have several years of work experience both in research institutes and in private companies in Germany, Spain and Hungary. I am eager to learn and challenge myself in interesting areas in the intersection of social and data science.
